%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>(opendatahub namespace)
    participant Worker0 as Worker Pod 0 (Master)<br/>29500/TCP TCP
    participant WorkerN as Worker Pod N<br/>various/TCP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Training Job Submission
    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS (auto-rotated certs)<br/>Auth: API Server TLS cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created / rejected

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 1 (cont): Controller Reconciliation
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Create Pods, Services, NetworkPolicies<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Update job status (ReplicaStatuses)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Worker0,WorkerN: Flow 2: Distributed Training (PyTorch)
    Worker0->>Worker0: 1. Listen on rendezvous port<br/>29500/TCP plaintext
    WorkerN->>Worker0: 2. Connect via Headless Service DNS<br/>29500/TCP plaintext
    WorkerN->>WorkerN: 3. Gradient sync (NCCL/Gloo)<br/>various/TCP plaintext

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 3: Metrics Collection
    Prometheus->>Controller: 1. GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 plaintext<br/>Auth: None (PodMonitor)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics
